Need for Speed: The Run competes across America.
Overview
A trip, initially carefree, is complicated by a series of improper carelessness of a routine journey during tomorrow's shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but this is of no use if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was meant to be done.
The new installment, to which the title is added The Run, raised high expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old racing series Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again.
We are also curious to know how the scenes inserted would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As usually happens in NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are careers that can be considered acceptable, but in total computation points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, mistakes cannot and cannot be called mistakes, but rather the incomprehensible sluggishness of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit at the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
That way, you don't even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries in the series.
It is therefore nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
In the mountains, however, care must be taken not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normally in a classic race), then you try to buy time (classic timed duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes the police appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than would be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context mentioned above, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the traces of the previous episodes.
That means that it is no longer a big deal today, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with quite a lot of action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, so good.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, collisions are no longer the same.
From games of this type you can't expect it to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight run or driving the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something doesn't go well, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, not even reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or stop.
It's the same when you get here, because it's programmed because the "surprise" will always happen right under your nose.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, without taking into account the moment, the same adversary will always advance you in the same place.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front of you, so at first you can mash the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it surely disappoints you immediately.
And it is a shame, because even if the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the classification in the race so that boredom doesn't fit, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to keep an eye on the gas pumps by the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supersports for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are careers in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
As you reach the upper level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending up with profile funds.
At the same time, there is an online Autolog function, which compares your results to those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you run in the dark along the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and suddenly, from behind you comes the metro convoy and takes you straight ahead.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game none even thought a bit or whether the authors actually take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a pity, then, that, in the most tense moments, image quality is reduced and, at times, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
Audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just because of his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game isn't over.
Fun is assured, but get ready because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University Carolina will participate in the concert "Terriper Students".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During this event, twenty chorales from high schools and universities will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Caroline University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choral of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the concert of high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of Czech jazz player Karel Rička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, the concert "Students of Velvet" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, with the participation of university chorals, including the chorus of the Carolina Uninversity.
The Academic Festa aims not only to celebrate the International Day of Students with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler High School.
All events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, impromptu student shows and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
