This was the work of the caleño who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Lofoscopist from Cali passed into history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a CTI lophoscopist from Cali passed into history as the man who confirmed the identity of the Farc's top chief: "Alfonso Cano", through the collation of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists working in the STI section, that week it was the turn of "availability" for Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to stay in the jungle for more than five days to reach the place where the bodies that had to be identified were located.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after completing the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopia, which is the study of friction skin, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactillar card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it because of its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was without a beard, dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the chief of the Farc.
In search of the print
For a dactyloscopist from the Sijín de Cali, the recognition given by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, at the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, without margin of error, that can become key in the resolution of crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lofoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals present false cards or have no papers.
We took their fingerprints and looked them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewels and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Footprints can also rule out or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
Recently they found a dead man, with liquor bottles all around him.
The investigation found that a family member could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a print on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A Dactyloscopist from the STI explained that in objects "prints are taken out with chemical or physical reagents".
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," said the STI expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI TV show.
Just as not all that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes trace.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is done.
